    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix MCS validation bounds check in M2AP setup response handling\n\n### Summary\nThe M2AP setup response processing in the eNB RRC layer was not properly validating MCS values before assigning them to the `signallingMCS_r9` ENUMERATED field. This caused invalid MCS selections that did not match channel quality or UE capability, leading to potential SIB13 configuration issues.\n\nThe bug was triggered when the MCE sent MCS values outside the valid range (0-3) for the ENUMERATED type, which maps to n2, n7, n13, n19 MCS levels respectively.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB_M2AP.c`: Added bounds checking for MCS values at all assignment points\n- Lines 458-459: Validate MCS in `rrc_M2AP_do_SIB1_MBMS_SIB13` \n- Line 568-569: Validate MCS in `rrc_M2AP_do_SIB1_MBMS_SIB13`\n- Line 991-992: Validate MCS in `rrc_M2AP_do_SIB23_SIB13`\n- Line 1136-1137: Validate MCS in `rrc_M2AP_do_SIB23_SIB2_SIB13` \n- Line 1246-1247: Validate MCS in `rrc_M2AP_do_SIB23_SIB2_SIB13`\n\nThe validation ensures MCS values are clamped to valid range, defaulting to MCS n7 (value 1) when out of bounds.\n"
}